Suppose that ''A'' is a matrix with singular value decomposition &lt;math>A = U\Sigma V^*&lt;/math> where

:&lt;math>
\begin{align}
U = &amp; \begin{bmatrix}
1/\sqrt 2 &amp; 1/\sqrt 2 &amp; 0 \\
1/\sqrt 2 &amp; -1/\sqrt 2 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1
\end{bmatrix} \\
\Sigma = &amp; \begin{bmatrix}
2 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1/2
\end{bmatrix} \\
V = &amp; \begin{bmatrix}
1/\sqrt 3 &amp; 0 &amp; 2/\sqrt 6 \\
1/\sqrt 3 &amp; 1/\sqrt 2 &amp; -1/\sqrt 6 \\
1/\sqrt 3 &amp; -1/\sqrt 2 &amp; -1/\sqrt 6
\end{bmatrix}
\end{align}
&lt;/math>

'''(a)''' Check all boxes that apply.

''U'' and ''V'' are: hermitian &amp;#x2610;, real symmetric &amp;#x2610;, unitary &amp;#x2610;, orthogonal &amp;#x2610;

&lt;math>\Sigma&lt;/math> is: hermitian &amp;#x2610;, real symmetric &amp;#x2610;, unitary &amp;#x2610;, orthogonal &amp;#x2610;

&lt;math>A^*A&lt;/math> and &lt;math>AA^*&lt;/math> are: hermitian &amp;#x2610;, real symmetric &amp;#x2610;, unitary &amp;#x2610;, orthogonal &amp;#x2610;

''A'' is: hermitian &amp;#x2610;, real symmetric &amp;#x2610;, unitary &amp;#x2610;, orthogonal &amp;#x2610;
